HOW TO MAKE MOLASSES.

Take pumpkins, boil them, press the juice out of them, and boil the
juice to a proper consistence. There is nothing else necessary. The
author of this book, John George Hohman has tasted this molasses,
thinking it was the genuine kind, until the people of the house told him
what it was.

